rust9 — Rust for 9front (self-hosted rustc). Changelog.
(`pac9 changelog rust9` shows this; newest first.)

0.2.0 — 2026-07-17
  First versioned release, and the one where the std port stops lying.

  A parity audit of the plan9 std backend found a row of stubs that returned
  a cheerful Ok/false while doing nothing — the exact shape of bug that only
  shows up in production. All fixed, all verified on bare metal:

    - Instant is now MONOTONIC. cc9's clock_gettime only has a realtime clock,
      so Instant could step backwards (timesync, settimeofday) and make
      elapsed() return 0 — hanging every timeout/backoff loop. Now monotonized
      in userspace; it never goes back.
    - File::try_lock / try_lock_shared are HONEST. They used to always "succeed"
      so single-instance guards and cache locks thought they held a lock they
      didn't. Now they return Unsupported instead of corrupting.
    - sync_all / sync_data actually fsync. They used to return Ok(()) doing
      nothing, so a crash after a "synced" commit lost data. Now durable on gefs.
    - Command env no longer LEAKS into the parent. Setting a child's env used to
      mutate the parent's /env (shared env group); now the child gets a private
      group (RFENVG), and env_clear / env_remove really scrub.
    - Network timeouts work: connect_timeout, set_read_timeout, set_write_timeout
      via Plan 9 alarm(2). A dead host returns in the deadline, not in minutes.
    - is_terminal() tracks the real tty (was hardwired false, so colours and
      progress bars never engaged). current_exe() and home_dir() return real
      values instead of Unsupported/None.
    - env::set_var is visible to env::vars() (vars() now reads /env live).

  Under the compiler, the cc9 runtime that your programs link also got the same
  honesty pass: durable fsync, correct O_APPEND, per-thread errno, corrected
  float formatting. Recompile to pick it up.

  Same rustc (1.98.0-dev, cranelift), same n9link, same layout — this is a std +
  runtime correctness release. Earlier unversioned installs read as '-';
  `pac9 upgrade rust9` moves them here.
